v0.1.1

* Initial release, support for Zabbix Client (Agent) on RedHat family 5 & 6.

v0.2.0

* Added support for Ubuntu (10.04, 12.04 & 14.04) & Debian (6/squeeze & 7/wheezy).
* Documented previously undocumented global variable that affects the version of zabbix that is installed.
* Fixed some documentation typos.

v0.2.1

* Added $zabbix::client::service_manage parameter as per Issue 1: https://github.com/kemra102/puppet-zabbix/issues/1
* Fixed support for RedHat, Scientific Linux & Oracle Linux as per Issue 2: https://github.com/kemra102/puppet-zabbix/issues/2
* Confirmed module running on Scientific Linux & Oracle Linux.

v0.3.0

* Added support for creating UserParameter's.
* Added server support. This will get a server up and running OK, some features here may be lacking and will be improved upon in future releases.
* Now provides facts for the versions of Zabbix Server & Zabbix Client installed on a node.

v0.3.1

* Added EL7 support now that Zabbix has it.
